Tile is a layout manager for creating user interfaces in 32/64 bit Windows.

Features:

Unit tested controls
- seriously, how many UI frameworks are actually unit tested?
Weighted allocation of pixel space 
- gracefully fill the screen or contract to minimal space.
User editable theme
- Caption colors
- Data colors
- Grid cell colors
- Grid row colors
- Grid cell / row spacing
- Toolbar colors
- Fonts (text, arrow, stock)
Flicker free display
- high update rates possible
Tiles
- Arrow
- Fill
- Glyph
- Text
Controls
- Button
- Check
- Combo
- Edit
- Toggle
- Tab
Generic Container
- Pane
- Scroll (scrollable flow)
- Tree (collapsible flow)
Type-Aware Container
- List
- Grid
Graphics
- Font
- Text
- Rectangles
- Polygons
- Polylines